        <p> Like you on <a href="{{ site.url }}/de/reiseblog/2018/02/01/workation-philippinen.html" target="_blank"> Have already read the beginning </a> , this trip was planned as an experiment for me and my employer. It was about seeing how much card making is already set to long -term teleworking. It was interesting for me whether I can concentrate on my job a full 8 hours during a trip and especially in beautiful and interesting places. I was also interested in how my work motivation changes when Steffi gets and she can laze about while I want to concentrate. </p>
        <p> Since I am a team leader of a 14-headed programmer team, take care of 2 trainees and also like to program myself, my expectations were split. I wanted to break through the usual structures and chase myself out of the comfort zone again. </p>
        <p> I definitely succeeded. <br> After only 2 weeks in the Philippines, I had a day when I would have loved to get back to the next plane and would have come home. That was all too much that day. </p>

    </div>
