    <div class="col-md-6">
        <p> It even turned out that the time shift of 7 or 6 hours was an unexpected advantage. Since I actually always get up in front of Steffi, I was often able to do up to 2 of my 8 hours of working time before she even put a foot out of bed. I got the hours again when we wanted to go out to eat in the evening, because then there was noon time in Hamburg and it regularly made it possible for me to work out. </p>
        <p> At the end of the experiment, we treated ourselves to 10 days of vacation. We fully used these for ourselves. We visited 5 more places. We enjoyed nature on Bohol, visited the Chocolate Hills as well as the Tarsiere and enjoyed the Loboc river at noon. Panglao was almost exclusively about water. I was diving several times and above all we treated ourselves to a wonderful and unforgettable day trip to Balicasag and Virgin Island, in which we saw turtles, saw real flying fish and enjoyed in the water, pineapple and fried sweet potatoes. In Manila we treated ourselves to one or the other souvenir on the way home and spent the last pesos that we had left. </p>
        <p> In the end it was all a successful journey with small lows, but all the bigger high. Several thousand photos have been taken again, especially from clown fishing. We were in a poor, but also very beautiful country with many friendly and in rural people. The Philippines are always worth a trip and if you do a little research, it will not be too expensive. To say it with Steffi&rsquo;s words: Philippines, always happy! </p>
